ackagingDataCalculator` through Logback’s public `LoggingEvent` / packaging-data API path.\n- Enables packaging data on a `LoggerContext`.\n- Sets the thread context class loader to the platform class loader so application stack frames cannot be loaded via TCCL.\n- This drives both remaining dynamic-access call sites:\n  - `ClassLoader#loadClass(String)` in `PackagingDataCalculator.loadClass`\n  - `Class#forName(String)` fallback in `PackagingDataCalculator.bestEffortLoadClass`\n- Asserts that packaging data is calculated for the test application stack frame.\n\nI did not modify or generate reachability metadata/native-image config.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0e9998d920f39f66016a057a5d1f6c81a1899704ddd4f7bdec\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 460, "output": 707, "cacheRead": 31744, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32911, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778743889935, "responseId": "resp_0e9998d920f39f66016a057a52acb881a1b88cebe02307c47d"}, "toolResults": []}
